## Your knobs (edit this block)

| Setting | Value | Notes |
|---------|-------|-------|
| **Default** | `auto` | `auto` · `poteto` · `ponytail` · `both` |
| **Short prompt (words)** | `80` | At or under → lean **ponytail** if complexity also low |
| **Long prompt (words)** | `200` | At or over → lean **poteto** if complexity also high |
| **QA gate** | `on` | `on` = ask when word count and complexity disagree; `off` = pick safer route silently |
| **Gate once per thread** | `on` | After user picks a mode, don't re-gate unless scope clearly escalates |

Count words in the **user's latest message only** (not agent replies). Attachments, pasted logs, or `@`-files add **complexity weight** but do not inflate the word count.

**Forced defaults (skip gate):** `poteto` / `ponytail` / `both` in the table bypass classification.

**User overrides in prompt (win over everything):**

| Say | Effect |
|-----|--------|
| `quick`, `ponytail only`, `just fix it` | Ponytail-only, no gate |
| `poteto`, `/poteto-mode`, `full process` | Full poteto, no gate |
| `both`, `full stack` | Poteto + ladder, no gate |
| `auto` | Re-run classification + gate if needed |

